</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[164,779,1675,1759]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">
The specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName authority="Latin" authorityName="Latin" box="[405,502,1706,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[405,502,1706,1727]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, Latin for spiny, refers to the spined aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
